WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:14.070 --> 00:00:15.070
Namaste!

00:00:15.070 --> 00:00:17.310
Three hundred and eighty!

00:00:17.310 --> 00:00:24.310
Once again, an opportunity to look back, questions,
opinions, complaints, … accusations!

00:00:24.310 --> 00:00:26.680
Let us see!

00:00:26.680 --> 00:00:29.060
I was unwell..

00:00:29.060 --> 00:00:33.610
I have missed the videos you had sent me..

00:00:33.610 --> 00:00:38.340
I will ensure I watch them regularly from
now on.. said a friend.

00:00:38.340 --> 00:00:48.980
This is just a sample of some of the unexpected
love that our viewers are showing me.

00:00:48.980 --> 00:00:55.410
Almost like a family member, almost like a
big brother, or a friend, it is truly heartening,

00:00:55.410 --> 00:00:58.660
when I read the messages they send me.

00:00:58.660 --> 00:01:01.180
Another person hit me with this!

00:01:01.180 --> 00:01:04.449
This gap.. seems to have become a bit too
long.

00:01:04.449 --> 00:01:07.880
It would be much better if you did this a
bit more frequently…

00:01:07.880 --> 00:01:08.880
And, guess who this was?

00:01:08.880 --> 00:01:10.390
The same person, who, not too long ago, said,
“You are sending it daily!

00:01:10.390 --> 00:01:12.100
And, I am not able to handle the load!”

00:01:12.100 --> 00:01:13.100
Same person!

00:01:13.100 --> 00:01:15.470
I don’t know what to do!

00:01:15.470 --> 00:01:16.600
Seriously!

00:01:16.600 --> 00:01:20.950
Another friend wrote to me and said, “This
is more manageable.

00:01:20.950 --> 00:01:26.990
Your original schedule was a bit unfair on
those who joined in a bit late.

00:01:26.990 --> 00:01:31.650
But now, thanks to you, I am able to catch
up.”

00:01:31.650 --> 00:01:43.430
So, yes, it is a push and pull between consistency,
regularity and accommodating the distracted

00:01:43.430 --> 00:01:44.430
world we live in.

00:01:44.430 --> 00:01:50.860
“There is too much stuff out there, I can’t
handle you daily!” says a group, on one

00:01:50.860 --> 00:01:51.860
side.

00:01:51.860 --> 00:01:56.149
And, another group, on the other side, demanding
that I give them more!

00:01:56.149 --> 00:02:00.570
There is a good dynamic tension, if you know
what I mean.

00:02:00.570 --> 00:02:06.329
One person complained about the Mother Teresa
pose that I had used in one of my thumbnails.

00:02:06.329 --> 00:02:09.920
“I personally feel it’s wrong, do you
really know who she was?” — and he went

00:02:09.920 --> 00:02:16.620
on to bring a political / religious touch
to the conversation.

00:02:16.620 --> 00:02:18.010
Please get this.

00:02:18.010 --> 00:02:24.520
There is no connection or correlation whatsoever
between this Quotidian series and those concepts.

00:02:24.520 --> 00:02:25.520
At all.

00:02:25.520 --> 00:02:31.910
So, you need not be concerned or worried that
I will talk politics or religion.

00:02:31.910 --> 00:02:34.110
I don’t know much about it.

00:02:34.110 --> 00:02:35.960
I am not interested in that.

00:02:35.960 --> 00:02:39.650
If that’s what you are here for, you are
in the wrong place.

00:02:39.650 --> 00:02:41.450
Here is another comment.

00:02:41.450 --> 00:02:48.880
“In Quotidian 370, you had talked about
a productivity trick, and I have been waiting

00:02:48.880 --> 00:02:51.920
since then, but you haven’t announced it,
why…!” they wanted to know.

00:02:51.920 --> 00:02:55.959
I think it was Mahatma Gandhi, they used to
tell this story about him.

00:02:55.959 --> 00:02:58.691
There was this little boy who ate a lot of
sweets.

00:02:58.691 --> 00:03:03.829
His Mom brings the kid over to the Mahatma
and asks him to give the boy some good advice.

00:03:03.829 --> 00:03:06.700
But, Gandhiji asks the Mom to bring the kid
over after fifteen days.

00:03:06.700 --> 00:03:10.950
And, promptly, after fifteen days, when the
child is brought again, he advises the boy

00:03:10.950 --> 00:03:14.150
with a simple and short “Dear Child, Do
not binge on sweets!”

00:03:14.150 --> 00:03:20.250
The mother asks him respectfully, “Why couldn’t
you tell this on that day?

00:03:20.250 --> 00:03:21.690
Why did you make me wait fifteen days?”

00:03:21.690 --> 00:03:28.060
To which, the Mahatma is supposed to have
responded: “The advice is easy to give.

00:03:28.060 --> 00:03:30.150
But, the implementation…

00:03:30.150 --> 00:03:33.030
To follow that advice is hard.

00:03:33.030 --> 00:03:37.080
Am I able to follow my own advice?

00:03:37.080 --> 00:03:38.840
I am struggling with it myself…

00:03:38.840 --> 00:03:41.190
I wanted to test it out myself first.”

00:03:41.190 --> 00:03:43.380
Exactly the same sentiment here.

00:03:43.380 --> 00:03:45.260
I am testing it out.

00:03:45.260 --> 00:03:47.670
I hit upon something very interesting.

00:03:47.670 --> 00:03:52.040
But, before I share it with you, I am testing
it out.

00:03:52.040 --> 00:03:53.980
Closed beta phase, you could call it.

00:03:53.980 --> 00:03:57.610
Davos wrote to me and commented about my dress.

00:03:57.610 --> 00:04:01.590
“What’s up with your dress, something
fell on it?

00:04:01.590 --> 00:04:05.190
Is there a story behind it?

00:04:05.190 --> 00:04:06.919
It looks a bit sweaty..!”

00:04:06.919 --> 00:04:11.979
Yes, I am shooting it in a place where there
is no good airconditioning.

00:04:11.979 --> 00:04:14.720
And summer is approaching, you see…

00:04:14.720 --> 00:04:18.400
You may be in Davos, .. lucky you!

00:04:18.400 --> 00:04:22.800
Rohith Kumar asked me — “How can I become
like you… bookreading?

00:04:22.800 --> 00:04:24.110
Or meditation?

00:04:24.110 --> 00:04:25.580
Or what should I do sir?”

00:04:25.580 --> 00:04:28.320
First of all, I am not some bigshot who deserves
being asked questions like “How should I

00:04:28.320 --> 00:04:29.320
become like you”…

00:04:29.320 --> 00:04:36.430
Secondly, if you would allow me to use your
own words and play around a bit…

00:04:36.430 --> 00:04:37.590
it is not “bookreading” OR “meditation”..

00:04:37.590 --> 00:04:43.730
Look at it as “meditating about the books
you read”.

00:04:43.730 --> 00:04:44.960
I will repeat.

00:04:44.960 --> 00:04:56.830
Rather than read ten different books on a
specific subject, read one book on that subject

00:04:56.830 --> 00:04:57.830
TEN TIMES.

00:04:57.830 --> 00:05:03.340
Recently, I read a book where I chanced upon
this beautiful, interesting, advice.

00:05:03.340 --> 00:05:10.120
Because, every time you read that book, something
more will sink in, and, a new dimension, a

00:05:10.120 --> 00:05:13.410
new perspective, you may hit upon.

00:05:13.410 --> 00:05:18.090
Rather than browse around in a desultory,
superficial fashion, probably it is better

00:05:18.090 --> 00:05:20.040
to dwell deep and analyse well.

